<h2>PC Mac or Linux desktops</h2>
<p>Browsers no longer support java applets, but
<a href=<!--#include virtual="/cgi-bin/applettag.cgi?tagname=jwsrawlink" -->
<img style="border: 0px solid ; width: 80px; height: 43px;" alt="java web start icon" title="click to launch boardspace with java web start"
 src="/images/java-web-star-icon.jpg"></a>&nbsp;will
launch the boardspace.net client directly, and will
leave a desktop icon you can use next time.&nbsp;</p>
<p>If clicking doesn't open the application, &nbsp;see <a href="needsjava.shtml">this page</a>.<br>
</p>
<h2>Android and IOS</h2>
<a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/boardspace.net/id1089274351?ls=1&amp;mt=8">
<img src="/images/download-on-the-app-store.png" alt="a free app on itunes" height="50" width="150"></a><a href="javascript:link('https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.boardspace',0)"><img src="/images/google-play-badge.jpg" alt="a free app on google play"> </a>
<p>The apps ought to work from any modern device, but
tablet-sized devices with at least 1G of memory are
recommended.&nbsp;&nbsp; Phones will work, but the screens are
annoyingly small. The CPUs, of mobile devices are pretty wimpy, so the
robots for many of games are noticeably weaker.<br>
</p>
The apps do not have any advertising or in-app purchases.&nbsp;
Just the games.
